[
    {
        "content": "<p>We really need to make it easier to convert an <code>ARef&lt;RustType&gt;</code> to/from a <code>*mut bindings::c_type</code>. Right now it requires a bunch of pointer casts.</p>",
        "id": 494356792,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1737119214
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I propose adding a <code>type RawType;</code> to the <code>AlwaysRefcounted</code> trait and having <code>ARef::into_raw</code> return <code>*mut T::RawType</code> rather than <code>NonNull&lt;T&gt;</code>.</p>",
        "id": 494356905,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1737119250
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sounds good to me</p>",
        "id": 494374734,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1737124644
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The same could apply to Opaque maybe?</p>",
        "id": 494374823,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1737124675
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Agreed.</p>",
        "id": 494374992,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1737124719
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/ARef.20to.2Ffrom.20raw.20pointer/near/494374823\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The same could apply to Opaque maybe?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I was going to suggest something like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">// could use a better name</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CWrapper</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">CType</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">as_raw_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CType</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CWrapper</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Opaque</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">CType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">as_raw_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but I guess we need a macro to <code>impl CWrapper</code> for things like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Opaque</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 494420027,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1737139890
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Could be a derive macro.</p>",
        "id": 494420117,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1737139923
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, that's what I'm thinking. Do you want to do it yourself or open an issue and help someone else?</p>",
        "id": 494420277,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1737139987
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I prefer Boqun's extra trait rather than adding to <code>AlwaysRefcounted</code> which may make sense for Rust types too.</p>",
        "id": 494464113,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1737161411
    }
